==Japanese==

===Etymology 1===
{{ja-kanjitab|あ|ちら|yomi=k,irr|alt=あちら}}
From archaic {{ja-r|あち}} + {{ja-r|等|ら|about; around; approximately}}.

====Pronoun====
{{ja-pos|pronoun|あちら}}

# [[there]]; that [[place]]
#: {{ja-x|皆さま、あちらをごらんください|みな さま、あちら を ごらん ください|Everybody, please look over '''there'''.}}
# {{q|polite}} that [[person]]
#: {{ja-x|あちらがお父さまですか|あちら が おとうさま です か|Is that you father? (polite)}}

=====Usage notes=====
* The hiragana spelling ([[あちら]]) is preferred to the kanji spelling ([[彼方]]), which is rarely used.

